    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bca45864_810a21ed",
        "filename": "luciexe/exe/props.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 124,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-28T23:54:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t want to think about this now :(. Plus, from https://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/docs/proto3#json\n\n\"An implementation may provide an option to use proto field name as the JSON name instead. Proto3 JSON parsers are required to accept both the converted lowerCamelCase name and the proto field name.\"\n\nThe problem is that we use not-proto parsers all over the place, and they assume the proto field names are the names in json. If we switch to the new library, we will need to add stupid [json_name] options to all of our protos first as part of the new library.\n\nOr we can refuse to switch until they add the option back, since their unmarshaller implementation must accept the non-stupid names anyway :)",
      "parentUuid": "3938c0b9_c32d6824",
